# Terminal hygiene (Cline)

- Prefer single compound commands over multiple sequential `execute_command` calls.
- Batch related git operations (`git add A && git commit -m "..."`) into one invocation.
- Avoid bare `git status` / `git log` — use `--short`, `--oneline -N`, or pipe output.
- On Windows PowerShell: `del` and `rm` behave differently than bash; prefer `Remove-Item` with comma-separated paths.
- If Cline freezes after a command completes, click Proceed — this is expected on both Windows and macOS.
- Close stale terminals in Cursor when the count exceeds 3 to prevent accumulation.